        {
          "feedback": "Exactly! TTFB measures the delay between sending the request and receiving the very first response byte. If the backend is slow to run queries and build the HTML, the browser is left waiting.",
          "isCorrect": true,
          "text": "The database taking too long to construct the dynamic HTML response."
        },
        {
          "feedback": "A large CSS file affects the page rendering speed and total download time, but it doesn't delay the initial response byte of the main HTML document itself.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "The main stylesheet being too large and complex."
